               <p>I recollect the prisoner, he was one of the five I took, I apprehended him at Hawksworth in company with White.</p>
               <p>Did he make any resistance? - None, he behaved as decently and as civily as people in that situation could: they stopped immediately, and gave themselves up, and confessed before the Justice, that they were such people.</p>
